独家 | 武汉肺炎康复患者出院后身体尚佳 医药费已退还。
The doctor's fees for Wuhan Pneumonia, a convalescent patient, have been refunded.
作者：陈婷 张家振 万笑天 来源：中国经营网。
Authors: Chen Ting Zhang Jing Wan Laughing Tianyuan: China operating network.
本报记者 陈婷 张家振 万笑天 武汉、北京报道新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情正进入新的发展阶段。
This reporter Chen Ting Zhang Jing Wan laugh days Wuhan, Beijing reported a new coronavirus pneumonia epidemic is entering a new stage of development.
官方最新统计数据显示，截至1月20日18时，境内累计报告新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎病例224例，其中确诊病例217例（武汉市198例，北京市5例，广东省14例）；疑似病例7例（四川省2例，云南省1例，上海市2例，广西壮族自治区1例，山东省1例）。
According to the latest official statistics, as of 18.00 January, 224 cases of pneumonia with new coronavirus infection had been reported in China, of which 217 were confirmed (198 in Wuhan city, 5 in Beijing and 14 in Guangdong Province); 7 were suspected cases (2 in Sichuan Province, 1 in Yunnan Province, 2 in Shanghai, 1 in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and 1 in Shandong Province).
日本通报确诊病例1例，泰国通报确诊病例2例，韩国通报确诊病例1例。
Japan reported 1 confirmed case, Thailand 2 confirmed cases and the Republic of Korea 1 confirmed case.
疑似病例隔离和确诊患者治疗情况也备受外界关注。
The isolation of suspected cases and the treatment of confirmed patients are also of concern.
1月10日～20日期间，《中国经营报》记者从多位肺炎患者家属处独家获悉，武汉市金银潭医院（武汉市医疗救治中心）已开始向患者退还部分住院预收款。
From January 10 to 20, the China Business Daily reporter learned exclusively from the families of many pneumonia patients that the gold and silver pool hospital in Wuhan (Wuhan Medical Treatment Center) had begun to refund some of the advance hospital receipts to the patients.
例如，1月10日，患者家属王（化姓）女士向本报记者提供的退款凭证显示，当天上午10点多，武汉市金银潭医院已分两次向其退还了共计1.2万元，其中一笔为1万元，另一笔为2000元。
For example, on January 10, Ms. Wang (not her real name), a family member of the patient, provided a refund certificate to our reporter showing that the gold and silver pool hospital in Wuhan had returned a total of 12,000 yuan to him in two instalments, one for 10,000 yuan and the other for 2,000 yuan.
（患者家属王女士向记者提供的退款截图）1月20日，另一位出院患者家属张先生告诉记者，此前预交共计4000元的住院费已在患者出院时全部退还，但是此前单独缴纳的伙食费没有退还。
Zhang, another family member of the discharged patient, told reporters on January 20 that the hospital fees, totalling 4,000 yuan, had been refunded when the patient left the hospital, but had not been refunded.
张先生表示，患者已出院一个星期，目前身体状况尚佳。
Zhang said the patient had been discharged from the hospital for a week and was in good health.
此前，本报记者曾先后多次深入华南海鲜批发市场和武汉市金银潭医院采访多位患者家属，就发病过程和诊疗情况进行了报道，并独家披露“个别患者已无力承担医药费”的状况。
Previously, the reporter had made a number of visits to the South China Wholesale Seafood Market and the Gold and Silver Pool Hospital in Wuhan City to interview a number of patients' families.
（详见中国经营网1月5日报道：对话武汉“病毒性肺炎”患者家属患者多为华南海鲜市场商户打工者 个别已无力承担医药费）多位患者家属表示已收到退款据王女士介绍，目前其弟弟王先生仍在武汉市金银潭医院接受治疗，尚未痊愈。
Dialogue Script 2 (s) 3 Family members of Wuhan patients suffering from viral pneumonia are mostly South China seafood market, and some workers are unable to afford medical expenses. Many patients' families said they had received refunds.
王先生因持续高烧于2019年12月31日下午两点左右从华中科技大学同济医学院附属同济医院转入武汉市金银潭医院，入住该院住院部南楼四楼。
Mr. Wang was transferred from Tongji Hospital, affiliated with Tongji Medical College, Central China University of Science and Technology, to Gold and Silver Pool Hospital in Wuhan at about 2: 00 p.m. on December 31, 2019.
此后，王女士和妹妹先后三次通过微信转账和银行刷卡的方式向武汉市金银潭医院预交了2000元、2000元和1万元的住院预收款。
Since then, Ms. Wang and her sister have paid 2,000 yuan, 2,000 yuan and 10,000 yuan in advance to Wuhan Gold and Silver Pool Hospital by micromail and bank debit card respectively.
“我通过微信一共交了12000元，另外2000元是我妹妹垫付的，这笔费用医院也一起退还了，但当时她是刷的信用卡，得一个月以后才能到账。
"I paid 12,000 yuan by micromail, and 2,000 yuan was advanced by my sister. The hospital returned the money, but it was a credit card she had brushed and it would not arrive until a month later.
”王女士告诉记者，目前其妹妹还没有收到这笔2000元的退款。
Ms Wang told reporters that her sister had not yet received the 2,000 yuan refund.
根据《中国经营报》记者此前报道，王先生在武汉华南海鲜批发市场一家经营鸡鸭鱼等冻品的档口打工，每天凌晨3点钟上班，从武汉市白沙洲农副产品大市场处进货，再运到华南海鲜批发市场进行售卖，傍晚5点半下班。
According to China Business Daily, Mr. Wang worked at the mouth of a frozen chicken, duck, fish and other frozen products in Wuhan South China Wholesale Seafood Market. He went to work at 3: 00 a.m. every morning, got his goods from the Peshazhu Agricultural and Byproducts Market in Wuhan and transported them to the South China Seafood Wholesale Market for sale.
“弟弟在华南海鲜批发市场打工一个月工资5000元，每天工作超过12个小时。
"My brother works at the South China Wholesale Seafood Market for 5,000 yuan a month, working more than 12 hours a day.
”王女士此前告诉本报记者，加上之前的治疗开销共花费约4.3万元，是王先生的两个姐姐在帮忙凑钱。
Ms. Wang told the paper that the cost of the treatment, plus previous treatment costs of about 43,000 yuan, is Mr. Wang's two older sisters to help collect money.
王女士向记者证实，目前缴纳的住院预收款已全数原路退还，并没有收到伙食费的退款。
Ms. Wang confirmed to reporters that the current advance payment of hospitalization has been returned to the original road, and did not receive a refund of food expenses.
“医院没有下发正式通知，只是跟患者说要家属拿发票去退钱。
"The hospital did not issue a formal notice, only told the patient to take the invoice to return the money.
”王女士表示，从1月8日开始，病房的护士就告诉患者让家属去退钱，说微信和支付宝缴款的费用马上就到账，通过银行卡缴费的会慢一些。
Since January 8, nurses in the ward have told patients to ask their families to return money, Ms. Wang said, noting that the cost of the letters and payments would arrive immediately and that payments through bank cards would be slower.
王女士此前告诉记者，弟弟今年44岁，一直在武汉租房子住。
Ms. Wang told reporters that her brother, 44, has been renting a house in Wuhan.
现在他已经没有钱治病了，是两个姐姐在帮忙凑钱。
Now that he had no money to treat his illness, his two sisters were helping to collect the money.
据其了解，在金银潭医院住院的病人大多是出苦力打工的，很多人东拼西凑，到处借钱治病。
According to its understanding, most of the patients hospitalized in the gold and silver pool hospital are laborers, many people patched together and borrowed money to treat the disease.
华南海鲜批发市场商户黄姓（化姓）大婶也向本报记者确认，其于1月10日已收到武汉市金银潭医院退还的1000元医疗费用。
Auntie Huang (not her real name), a wholesaler in South China Seafood Market, also confirmed to the reporter that on January 10, she had received from the Gold and Silver Pool Hospital in Wuhan the 1000 yuan medical expenses.
“当时医院让先预交6000元，手里没钱就先只交了1000元。
"At that time the hospital let the first 6000 yuan, the hand has no money on the first only paid 1000 yuan.
”黄姓大婶告诉本报记者，那时候因为交的是现金，医院就没有给退款凭据，直接全部给的现金。
"Auntie Huang told the reporter that at that time because the cash was handed over, the hospital did not give refund credentials, directly all the cash.
据黄姓大婶介绍，夫妻两人都在华南海鲜批发市场东区卖猪肉副食产品。
According to Auntie Huang, both husband and wife are selling pork products in the eastern part of the South China Seafood Wholesale Market.
2019年12月31日，其丈夫因反复发烧从其他医院转到武汉市金银潭医院。
On 31 December 2019, her husband was transferred from another hospital with recurrent fever to the Gold and Silver Pool Hospital in Wuhan.
“不排除有限人传人的可能”根据国家卫健委官网1月19日晚消息，近日陆续向全国各省派出工作组，指导做好新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情防控相关工作。
"Without excluding the possibility of a limited human-to-human transmission," a team has been dispatched to all provinces in recent days to guide the prevention and control of the new coronavirus infection.
专家研判认为，当前疫情仍可防可控，但新型冠状病毒传染来源尚未找到，疫情传播途径尚未完全掌握，病毒变异仍需严密监控。
Experts concluded that the current outbreak can still be controlled, but the new coronavirus transmission source has not been found, the spread of the disease is not fully grasped, the virus mutations still need to be closely monitored.
记者梳理发现，随着疫情发展，武汉市卫健委对外通报的频率和口径也出现了细微变化。
Reporters carded to find that, along with the development of the epidemic, Wuhan Health Commission reported to the outside frequency and caliber has also changed slightly.
在通报频率方面，从1月11日开始变为一日一通报，在口径方面也从此前的“未见明显人传人”改为“不排除有限人传人的可能”。
In terms of frequency of communication, from 11 January to 1 day notification, also from the previous "no obvious person-to-person" to "do not exclude the possibility of limited human-to-human transmission."
例如，1月14日，武汉市卫健委在“新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情知识问答”中回应：现有的调查结果表明，尚未发现明确的人传人证据，不能排除有限人传人的可能，但持续人传人的风险较低。
For example, on January 14, the Wuhan Health Care Commission responded in a question-and-answer session on the knowledge of pneumonia related to a new coronavirus infection: The available investigation results show that no clear human-to-human evidence has been found and the possibility of a limited person-to-person transmission cannot be ruled out.
武汉市卫健委在最新通报中表示，武汉市在不断规范各级各类医疗机构预检分诊和发热门诊运行的基础上，按照新修订的新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎诊疗方案，进一步加大了新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疑似病例筛查力度，同时进一步完善检测方案，优化检测流程，加快了检测速度。
According to the newly revised diagnosis and treatment plan for coronavirus infection, the city of Wuhan has further expanded the screening of suspected cases of pneumonia due to the new coronavirus infection on the basis of constantly standardizing the pre-screening and heating clinics at all levels and in accordance with the newly revised diagnosis and treatment plan for coronavirus infection.
另外，针对近期武汉市发生新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情，为强化技术交流，应港澳台地区相关部门请求，1月13～14日，武汉市卫生健康委接待了港澳台地区专家组实地考察。
In addition, in response to the recent outbreak of a new coronavirus infection in Wuhan, and in order to strengthen technical exchanges, the Wuhan Health and Wellness Commission received a field visit from the Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan Expert Group on January 13-14.
1月20日，武汉市卫健委在官网公布了全市发热门诊医疗机构和定点救治医疗机构名单。
On January 20, Wuhan Health Care Commission in the official website announced the city's heating out-patient medical institutions and designated medical institutions list.
包括全市发热门诊61家，其中中心城区41家，新城区20家，市管医院16家；全市定点医疗机构9家，其中中心城区定点医疗机构为市金银潭医院、市肺科医院、市汉口医院，远城区定点医疗机构为各区人民医院。
There are 61 fever clinics in the city, including 41 in central urban areas, 20 in new urban areas and 16 in municipal hospitals, and 9 designated medical institutions throughout the city, of which the designated medical institutions in the central urban areas are the City Gold and Silver Pool Hospital, the City Lung Hospital and the City Hankou Hospital.
同时，武汉市组建了有25名专家成员的省市联合医疗救治专家组，以加强发热病例的处置能力。
At the same time, Wuhan has set up 25 expert members of the provincial and municipal joint medical treatment expert group to strengthen the capacity to deal with calorific cases.
对于治疗费用的退还情况和具体安排，本报记者先后联系了武汉市金银潭医院和武汉卫健委相关宣传负责人，双方均表示“权威信息会通过武汉卫健委官网及时对外发布”。
For the refund of treatment costs and specific arrangements, the reporter has contacted Wuhan City Gold and Silver Pool Hospital and Wuhan Health Commission propaganda officials, both said "authoritative information will be issued in time through Wuhan Health Officers' Network."
（编辑：曹学平 校对：颜京宁）。
